Or you could use atomic swaps on the initialized bit. That's both cheaper and simpler.<p>psuedocode:<p><pre><code>    member atomic32 init
    member mutex lock
    member obj ptr


    membarrier()
    if (atomic_load(&init)) {
      return ptr
    } else {
      locked_init()
      atomic_save(&init, 1)
      membarrier()
    }
</code></pre>
Not an expert, use this at your own risk.
